Small Hope x2<br />
Men of Rhun x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Free Peoples Stratgey- I have Aragorn starting because he is a big tough guy, and i can draw companions easily. Next, i do not have any fortifactions because i got very tired of them, even though they were good! The basic idea of this group of amazing knights is to win the battles. ou have all of the possesions so you can equip the baddies like elendil and aragorn. Next you have isildur who also pumps them up, and if ever in trouble{doubt it} you can use strength of numenor. You have armor of the citadel, to preven those damage bonuses. Elendil, gives resistance to your men. If your really in a need of assistance, you can use duty of two, which heals your companions. You also have athelas, to keep you traveling on the adventure path. Faramir let&#39;s you see your top ten cards and lets you play a knight.<br />
<br />
Shadow Strategy- It is basically a easterling token adding. The sites help you a lot with adding burdens. and you have guard and lieutenant to add burdens. I threw trooper in there to make him fierce and damage +1. In case you can&#39;t get enough burdens, you can overwhelm ver easily. Easterling skirmisher adds twighlight. Captain supports your troops with more strength. Easterling Pillager adds twighlight. Easterling Army also supports your troops with strength, just not as well.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
